Steps to get started with Django on Heroku
1. Create an account at heroku.com
2. Create and start a python virtualenv http://pypi.python.org/pypi/virtualenv
    a) easy_install virtualenv #first time only
    b) mkdir ~/Documents/PythonEnv/ && cd ~/Documents/PythonEnv/
    c) virtualenv --no-site-packages project_name
    d) source ~/Documents/PythonEnv/project_name/bin/activate
3. git clone git@github.com:rfadams/python-django-heroku.git ~/projects/project_name
4. cd ~/projects/project_name && pip install -r requirements.txt
5. python web/manage.py runserver
6. Install the heroku CLI http://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/heroku-command
7. heroku create --stack cedar project_name
8. heroku open
 


#Optional
9. mysqladmin -u DBUSER -p create projectdb